.TH TGLFS-SEARCH 1 "March 2026" "tglfs 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tglfs-search \- search TGLFS file cards in Saved Messages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tglfs search
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIquery\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Looks up TGLFS file cards in Telegram Saved Messages. With no query, the command lists the first page of all file cards. Search results include complete and incomplete file cards.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --limit <n>
Maximum number of file cards to fetch. Default:
.B 50.
.TP
.B --offset-id <msgId>
Resume from a Telegram message-id cursor returned by a previous search page.
.TP
.B --sort <sort>
Sort the current result window. Values:
.BR date_desc ,
.BR date_asc ,
.BR name_asc ,
.BR name_desc ,
.BR size_desc ,
.BR size_asc .
.TP
.B --json
Emit machine-readable JSON.
.SH AI AGENT NOTES
The plain-text output is for humans. Agents should prefer
.B --json
and can paginate statelessly with
.B --offset-id.
The search cursor follows Telegram message order, even when the displayed page is client-side sorted.
